src/routing/.token
*.gbrain-lock
*.snapshot

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Vault: the project keeps its brain in vault/, which is its OWN embedded git
# repo (vault/.git). An outer repo cannot track files inside an embedded repo —
# git would only record a useless gitlink (a bare SHA pointing at the private
# vault repo) and the .gitkeep placeholders inside it are unreachable. So the
# whole tree is ignored here. NO vault content — real OR placeholder — is ever
# committed to the client repo. The client's empty folders are created at
# runtime: launch.bat / setup.bat make vault/raw/{s1,s2,s3}; the /ingest
# endpoint makes vault/inbox. Fail-closed: this guarantees zero MNPI leak.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
vault/

# Read-only clones used for audit only (not part of the runtime tree)
repos-audit/

# Forks placed at project root by user — track via SHAS pin file, not source
ClawXRouter/
privacy-filter/

# Junk LICENSE written by earlier failed curl
LICENSE
